Generic single-database configuration.

Run from ``backend/`` (with ``.env`` or env vars set):

  alembic upgrade head
  alembic current
  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add column"
  alembic downgrade -1

If you see ``DuplicateTable: relation "tickers" already exists``, the schema is
already there (e.g. from ``create_all``). Do **not** run ``upgrade`` again — stamp:

  alembic stamp head
  alembic current

``stamp`` only writes the revision row in ``alembic_version``; it does not change tables.
